{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, we analysed particular instances within the validation set where using refinement improved on the original generated lay report and where using refinement resulted in worse output to confirm this.",
    "Specific examples are noted in Appendix D. We noticed the feedback model tended to suggest the use of more technical medical terms despite being explicitly instructed that the aim was the generation of lay (i.e.",
    "readable) reports, which could affect readability scores.",
    "Furthermore, Table 7 shows that poor suggestions could result in less accurate reports (e.g.",
    "'long-term changes' generated by the SFT model vs. 'ongoing changes' generated by the refinement model to describe the term, 'chronic' due to the feedback describing the former as 'vague')."
  ]
}